'''2010年瓜地马拉市沉洞'''是在[[危地馬拉|危地馬拉]][[危地馬拉省|危地馬拉省]][[瓜地马拉市|瓜地马拉市]]佐纳2区出現的一个约20米宽、30米深的灾难性[[沉洞|沉洞]]，該沉洞吞噬了一幢三层楼高的工厂和一位保安<ref name="Christian Science Monitor">{{cite news | url=http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Americas/2010/0601/Guatemala-City-sinkhole-so-big-so-round-it-doesn-t-seem-real | title=Guatemala City sinkhole so big, so round it 'doesn't seem real' | work=Christian Science Monitor | date=2010-06-01 | agency=Christian Science Monitor | accessdate=2013-12-11 | last=Fieser | first=Ezra | location=Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic | archivedate=2013-10-01 | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131001030543/http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Americas/2010/0601/Guatemala-City-sinkhole-so-big-so-round-it-doesn-t-seem-real }}</ref><ref name="Huffington Post">{{cite news | url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/03/01/killer-sinkholes-deaths_n_2791634.html | title=Killer Sinkholes: Unexpected Holes Swallow Entire Families, Cars And Homes (PHOTOS) | work=Huffington Post | date=2013-03-01 | agency=Huffington Post | accessdate=2013-12-11 | author=Campbell, Andy | archivedate=2013-03-04 | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130304164705/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/03/01/killer-sinkholes-deaths_n_2791634.html }}</ref><ref name="National Geographic 1">{{cite news | url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/06/100603-science-guatemala-sinkhole-2010-humans-caused/ | title=Guatemala Sinkhole Created by Humans, Not Nature | work=National Geographic | date=2010-06-03 | agency=National Geographic | accessdate=2013-12-11 | author=Than, Ker | archivedate=2013-11-11 | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111023401/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/06/100603-science-guatemala-sinkhole-2010-humans-caused/ }}</ref><ref name="National Geographic 2">{{cite news |url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/06/100601-sinkhole-in-guatemala-2010-world-science/# |title=Sinkhole in Guatemala: Giant Could Get Even Bigger |work=National Geographic |date=2010-06-01 |agency=National Geographic |accessdate=2013-12-11 |author=Than, Ker |archivedate=2013-10-27 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131027182954/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/06/100601-sinkhole-in-guatemala-2010-world-science/%23 }}</ref><ref name="NOWnews">{{cite news |title=瓜地馬拉驚見「地獄之門」 3層樓高工廠被吞噬 |url=https://www.nownews.com/news/20100602/708054 |accessdate=2018-07-16 |publisher=NOWnews今日新聞 |date=2010-06-02 |archive-date=2018-07-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180716140557/https://www.nownews.com/news/20100602/708054 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，造成至少15人死亡。这个沉洞的形成有多个不同的原因，其中包括2010年的[[热带风暴阿加莎|热带风暴阿加莎]]、[[帕卡亚火山|帕卡亚火山]]爆发，以及下水管道的破裂和泄露等。多位地质学家要求[[危地马拉|危地马拉]]政府加大对下水道系统的检查频率，并对沉洞的填充提出了新的方案。

== 背景 ==
总体而言，瓜地马拉市出现沉洞的风险很高而且无法预测<ref>{{cite web | archivedate=2013-10-21 | deadurl=no | url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/06/photogalleries/100604-sinkhole-pictures-around-the-world-guatemala-city/ | title=Guatemala Sinkhole, 2010 | date=2010-06-04 | accessdate=2013-12-11 | author=Minard, Anne | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131021163552/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/06/photogalleries/100604-sinkhole-pictures-around-the-world-guatemala-city/ }}</ref>。2007年该市就曾出现过一个类似的沉洞，深度更达到100米<ref name="Waltham2008">{{cite journal |last=Waltham |first=T. |year=2008 |archivedate=2013-12-11 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211125644/http://qjegh.lyellcollection.org/isi-links//qjegh/41/3/291?rt=yes |url=http://qjegh.lyellcollection.org/content/41/3/291.abstract |title=Sinkhole hazard case histories in karst terrains |journal=Quarterly Journal of Engineering Geology and Hydrogeology |volume=41 |issue=3 |pages=291-300 |access-date=2013-12-11 }}</ref><ref name="Halliday2007">{{cite journal |last=Halliday |first=W. R. |year=2007 |title=Pseudokarst in the 21st century |journal=Journal of Cave and Karst Studies |volume=69 |issue=1 |pages=103-113}}</ref>。2007年瓜地马拉市的沉洞是由于[[下水道|下水道]]中的液体对该市未胶结的沉积[[火山灰|火山灰]]、[[石灰岩|石灰岩]]和其它[[火山碎屑岩|火山碎屑岩]]的侵蚀作用引起<ref name="Waltham2008" /><ref name="Halliday2007" />。自那以后，该市对废水和径流的处理方式有所改进，管道周围的这一危害性也就相应得到了缓解<ref name="discovery.com">{{cite web | archivedate=2013-10-29 | url=http://news.discovery.com/earth/dont-call-the-guatemala-sinkhole-a-sinkhole.htm | title=Don't Call The Guatemala Sinkhole a Sinkhole | date=2010-06-04 | accessdate=2013-12-11 | author=Reilly, Michael | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029001440/http://news.discovery.com/earth/dont-call-the-guatemala-sinkhole-a-sinkhole.htm }}</ref>。同時，連场暴雨的雨水渗入地下並进一步溶解瓜地马拉市的地下岩层，也促进了沉洞的坍塌<ref name="National Geographic 3">{{cite web | url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2007/02/070226-sinkhole-photo/ | title=Photo in the News: Giant Sinkhole Swallows Guatemala Homes | publisher=National Geographic | date=2007-02-26 | accessdate=2013-12-11 | author=Chamberlain, Ted | archivedate=2013-10-25 | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131025132747/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2007/02/070226-sinkhole-photo/ }}</ref><ref name="NBC News">{{cite news | archivedate=2013-10-21 | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131021143030/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/17303991/ns/world_news-americas/t/third-body-pulled-giant-sinkhole/ | url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/17303991/ns/world_news-americas/t/third-body-pulled-giant-sinkhole/ | title=Third body pulled from giant sinkhole | work=NBC News | date=2007-02-24 | agency=NBC | accessdate=2013-12-11 }}</ref>。2010年这个沉洞的坍塌也有着类似的原因<ref name="National Geographic 4">{{cite web | url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/06/100601-sinkhole-in-guatemala-2010-world-science/ | title=Sinkhole in Guatemala: Giant Could Get Even Bigger | publisher=National Geographic | date=2010-06-01 | accessdate=2013-12-11 | author=Than, Ker | archivedate=2013-10-27 | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131027182954/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/06/100601-sinkhole-in-guatemala-2010-world-science/ }}</ref>。

== 形成 ==
=== 排污管道 ===
[[File:Tropical_Storm_Agatha_Guatemala_Flooding.jpg|thumb]]
瓜地马拉市是建立在火山[[浮岩|浮岩]]沉积层上，沉洞也是因此形成<ref name="National Geographic 1" />。这些沉积层密度较低，而且未经固结，所以很容易受到[[侵蚀作用|侵蚀]]<ref name="National Geographic 1" />。据[[达特茅斯学院|达特茅斯学院]][[地质学家|地质学家]]山姆·博尼斯（{{lang|en|Sam Bonis}}）所称，由于城市区划法规和建筑规范较为宽松，所以只要漏水的水管长时间没有得到修理，就足以达到沉洞形成所需要的条件<ref name="National Geographic 1" />。博尼斯表示，瓜地牙拉市的这个沉洞名不符实，因为沉洞的形成存在自然因素，但这一个主要是人为造成的<ref name="National Geographic 1" />。此外博尼斯还称，沉洞通常都是从石灰岩上形成，但瓜地马拉市地下数百米都不存在石灰岩<ref name="National Geographic 1" />，他因此建议将这个沉洞改称为某种与管道有关的名称<ref name="National Geographic 1" />。

=== 热带风暴阿加莎 ===
{{main|热带风暴阿加莎}}
[[File:Agatha_2010_track.png|thumb]]
2010年5月24日，气象预测部门在[[哥斯达黎加|哥斯达黎加]]西海岸发现了一个[[低气压|低压]][[低压槽|槽]]<ref name="TCR">{{cite web |author=Jack L. Beven |publisher=National Hurricane Center |date=2011-01-10 |accessdate=2013-12-11 |title=Tropical Storm Agatha Tropical Cyclone Report |archivedate=2012-10-25 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025001445/http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/pdf/TCR-EP012010_Agatha.pdf |url=http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/pdf/TCR-EP012010_Agatha.pdf |format=[[PDF|PDF]] }}</ref>。5月29日，这股低气压增强为热带风暴，[[国家飓风中心_(美国)|美国国家飓风中心]]因此将其命名为阿加莎（{{lang|en|Agatha}}）<ref name="PA2">{{cite web |author=Stacey Stewart and Todd Kimberlain |publisher=National Hurricane Center |date=2010-05-29 |accessdate=2013-12-11 |title=Tropical Storm Agatha Public Advisory Two |archivedate=2012-10-24 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024055447/http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2010/ep01/ep012010.public.002.shtml |url=http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2010/ep01/ep012010.public.002.shtml? }}</ref>。当天稍後，系统在略有增强后以每小时75公里的风速[[登陆_(气象学)|登陆]][[墨西哥|墨西哥]]和[[危地马拉|危地马拉]]边境地區<ref>{{cite web |author=Lixion A. Avila and John Cangialosi |publisher=National Hurricane Center |date=2010-05-29 |accessdate=2013-12-11 |title=Tropical Storm Agatha Tropical Cyclone Update |archivedate=2012-10-24 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024055523/http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2010/ep01/ep012010.update.05292233.shtml |url=http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2010/ep01/ep012010.update.05292233.shtml? }}</ref>。到了5月30日早上，风暴中心已经越过了[[中美洲|中美洲]]地势最高的地区，并消散成低层[[大气环流|环流]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Daniel Brown |publisher=National Hurricane Center |date=2010-05-30 |accessdate=2013-12-11 |title=Tropical Depression Agatha Discussion Five (Final) |url=http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2010/ep01/ep012010.discus.005.shtml? |archivedate=2012-10-24 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024055537/http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2010/ep01/ep012010.discus.005.shtml |deadurl=no }}</ref>。风暴带来的暴雨拓宽了空腔体，最终导致沉洞的坍塌<ref name="National Geographic 1" />。

=== 帕卡亚火山爆发 ===
[[File:volcan-de-pacaya.jpg|thumbnail]]
{{Main|帕卡亚火山}}
5月27日，阿加莎成为热带低气压两天前，位于瓜地马拉市以南约40公里的帕卡亚火山发生爆发，至少造成一人死亡，并给附近地区笼罩了一层厚厚的火山灰<ref>{{cite web | archivedate=2013-12-09 | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131209171440/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/05/28/guatemala-volcano-pacaya-_n_593583.html#s94957&title=Guatemala_Volcano | url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/05/28/guatemala-volcano-pacaya-_n_593583.html#s94957&title=Guatemala_Volcano | title=Guatemala Volcano: Pacaya Eruption Kills TV Reporter, 3 Missing (PHOTOS) | publisher=Huffington Post | date=2010-05-28 | accessdate=2013-12-11 | author=Llorica, Juan }}</ref>。这次喷发还促使政府关闭了该国的国际机场<ref>{{cite web | url=http://edition.cnn.com/2010/WORLD/americas/07/22/guatemala.volcano/index.html | title=Guatemala warns of volcano danger | publisher=CNN | date=2010-07-22 | accessdate=2013-12-11 | archivedate=2010-11-01 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101101191052/http://edition.cnn.com/2010/WORLD/americas/07/22/guatemala.volcano/index.html | deadurl=no }}</ref>。随着阿加莎的形成，人们担心风暴带来的过量降雨可能会令情况更加严峻并引发[[火山泥流|火山泥流]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Robert Campbell |publisher=Reuters |date=2010-05-29 |accessdate=2013-12-11 |title=Guatemala girds for first Pacific storm of season |archivedate=2013-12-11 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211145108/http://www.worldbulletin.net/?aType=haberYazdir&ArticleID=59223&tip= |url=http://www.worldbulletin.net/?aType=haberYazdir&ArticleID=59223&tip= }}</ref>。火山灰导致地下管道被[[火山灰|烟尘]]阻塞，增大了管道出现破裂的可能性<ref name="National Geographic 1" /><ref name="National Geographic 2" />。

== 坍塌和后果 ==
当地一家《时针》（{{lang|es|''La Hora''}}）日报的[[记者|记者]]玛丽拉·卡斯坦尼欧（{{lang|es|Mariela Castañón}}）在报道中称地面突然间就坍塌了，瞬间吞噬了一幢三层高的工厂和一位保安，电线杆也被拖入地下。政府称暂无法确定这位保安是否已经死亡<ref name="Christian Science Monitor" /><ref name="La Hora">{{cite news |url=http://www.lahora.com.gt/index.php/nacional/guatemala/reportajes-y-entrevistas/131879-hundimientos-atraen-a-la-prensa-extranjera |title=Hundimientos atraen a la prensa extranjera |date=2010-07-17 |newspaper=La Hora |accessdate=2013-12-11 |last=Castañón |first=Mariela |archivedate=2013-12-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211150010/http://www.lahora.com.gt/index.php/nacional/guatemala/reportajes-y-entrevistas/131879-hundimientos-atraen-a-la-prensa-extranjera }}</ref>。

这个沉洞在瓜地马拉市的佐纳2区坍塌，至少造成15人死亡，还有300位居民的生命受到威胁<ref name="Huffington Post" />。由于排污管道在此次坍塌中扮演了至关重要的角色，因此包括山姆·博尼斯在内的多位地质学家都要求危地马拉政府增大对下水道系统的检查频率<ref name="National Geographic 2" />。

据官方消息称，本次沉洞的坍塌与2007年该市的另一个沉洞存在类似之处，都有可能是因为排污管道破裂而引起<ref name="National Geographic 2" />。

更大范围内，当阿加莎在当地造成人员伤亡后，危地马拉立即宣布进入紧急状态<ref>{{cite web |author=Herbert Hernandez |work=Reuters |publisher=MSNBC |date=2010-05-29 |accessdate=2013-12-11 |title=Pacific storm Agatha's rains kill four in Guatemala |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/05/29/us-storm-centralamerica-idUSTRE64S1A620100529 |archivedate=2013-12-11 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211151224/http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/05/29/us-storm-centralamerica-idUSTRE64S1A620100529 }}</ref>。5月31日，政府开始部署国家援助，全国各地都开设了对风暴受害者的捐赠接收站点。据{{link-en|联合国人道主义事务协调办公室|United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs}}消息称，危地马拉的学校将至少关闭到6月4日<ref name="OCHA1">{{cite web |author=Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs |publisher=Red de Información Humanitaria |date=2010-05-31 |accessdate=2012-03-08 |title=América Central - Tormenta Tropical Agatha Informe de Situación #1 |archivedate=2012-03-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308065324/http://redhum.org/archivos/pdf/ID_7734_GG_Redhum-OCHA-Sitrep1_-_Tropical_Storm_Agatha-by_ROLAC-ESP-20100531.pdf |url=http://redhum.org/archivos/pdf/ID_7734_GG_Redhum-OCHA-Sitrep1_-_Tropical_Storm_Agatha-by_ROLAC-ESP-20100531.pdf |format=PDF }}</ref>。

=== 填补沉洞 ===
沉洞坍塌后，当地立即计划用[[水泥|水泥]]、[[石灰岩|石灰岩]]和[[水|水]]组成的复合材料对其进行填充。这种材料在当地被称为“{{lang|en|lodocreto}}”，曾被用来填补2007年的瓜地马拉市沉洞。但是也有報道認為另一种被一些地质学家称之为「分级过滤技术」的方法可能效果会更好，这种方法将使用连续多层大石块、小石头和沙砾来填充沉洞，同時也因为如果用水泥来填补沉洞有機會会将地下径流发散到其他区域，提高该市其他地区将来发生沉洞的可能性。而在分级过滤的方式下，水可以直接渗过去<ref name="slate">{{cite web | archivedate=2013-09-28 | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928183206/http://www.slate.com/articles/news_and_politics/explainer/2010/06/how_to_fix_a_giant_sinkhole.html | url=http://www.slate.com/articles/news_and_politics/explainer/2010/06/how_to_fix_a_giant_sinkhole.html | title=How To Fix a Giant Sinkhole | publisher=Slate Magazine | date=2010-06-04 | accessdate=2013-12-11 | author=Palmer, Brian }}</ref>。

